      "ESSeqNum": 0,
      "FacilityID": 1000093622,
      "SummaryText": "Scott Medical Products/Airgas Specialty gases Fluorine Building operates an Industrial Gas distribution and storage facility for Fluorine and Sulfur Tetrafluoride. \r\n\r\nThe toxic characteristics of Fluorine and Sulfur Tetrafluoride make it necessary to observe certain precautions when handling. \r\n\r\nOverall, the prevention of exposures and reducing the threat to associates personal health, as well as reducing the threat to nearby members of the community is the main goal of incorporating this Risk Management Plan into our daily operations. \r\n\r\nIt is Scott Medical Products/Airgas Specialty Gases policy to adhere to all applicable local, state, and federal rules and regulations. \r\n\r\nOverall safety of the facility depends upon the manner in which products are stored and handled, combined in coordination with the operations and maintenance procedures provided to all personnel responsible for the use of the systems. \r\n\r\nWritten policies and procedures for handling these products are followed each day. Maintenance when necessary is performed by qualified Airgas personnel or contracted out to pre-qualified companies who have trained personnel in the proper maintenance of the systems. \r\n\r\nThe mechanical integrity of the systems is maintained in accordance with all good engineering practices. \r\n\r\nAirgas maintenance personnel and contractors have access to the Operations & Maintenance manuals for all systems. \r\n\r\nThis facility has a Process Safety Management plan which is incorporated into the daily routine to comply with the Level 3 Prevention Program requirements.\r\n\r\nThe facility follows the Airgas Health, Safety, and Environmental program that includes items such as Lockout/Tag out, Hazard Communication, Contractor Safety, etc. \r\n\r\nThe facility has an Emergency Action Plan in place to aid in the response of accidental releases and natural disasters that may affect the facility.\r\n\r\nThe Bucks county LEPC and the Plumsteadville Fire Department have been provided copies of this"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 1000093622,
      "SummaryText": "plan. If a release were to occur at this location, associates would be notified of the release by activation of the audible alarm and muster at the evacuation point for a head count and notify the Plumsteadville Fire Department if necessary. \r\n\r\nThe Plumsteadville  Fire Department is the primary response agency to a release at this location and is trained in Hazardous Materials operations. \r\n\r\nThe distance to the endpoint for the worst case scenario is 0.6 miles.\r\n\r\nThe area surrounding the facility is considered urban. \r\n\r\nThis release scenario could impact approximately 1054 persons in a 0.6 mile radius. This information was determined using RMP*Comp and MARPLOT software. \r\n\r\nThe distance to endpoint for the alternate release scenario is 0.3 miles.\r\n\r\nThis release scenario could impact approximately 6 persons in a 0.3 mile radius.\r\n\r\nThis information was determined using RMP*Comp and MARPLOT software."
    }
